SIMPLE: riotous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Riotous
<hw>Ri"ot*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>rioteux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Involving, or engaging in,
riot; wanton; unrestrained; luxurious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The younger son . . . took his journey into a far country, and
there wasted his substance with <qex>riotous</qex> living.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke xv. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Partaking of the nature of an unlawful assembly or
its acts; seditious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ri"ot*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ri"ot*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riotry</ent>⟦br⟧
